ZH: 何必为了一点小事情而生气呢？
EN: Why get angry over such a small matter?

ZH: 何必为难自己，别人的想法无关紧要。
EN: Why bother troubling yourself with other people's thoughts?

ZH: 何必把自己的幸福建立在别人的失落之上？
EN: Why build your own happiness on others' disappointments?

ZH: 在这个时代，何必拘泥于传统的观念和方法？
EN: In this era, why cling to traditional ideas and methods?

ZH: 何必为了面子，去做违背良心的事情？
EN: Why sacrifice your conscience for the sake of reputation?

ZH: 想要快乐，何必非要拥有所有的物质财富呢？
EN: To be happy, why must you possess all material wealth?

ZH: 何必追求完美，不完美也可以是一种美味呢。
EN: Why pursue perfection when imperfection can also be delicious?

ZH: 何必放弃自己的梦想，为别人过着无聊的生活呢？
EN: Why give up on your dreams to live a boring life for others?

ZH: 当做了错事，何必不肯承认并道歉呢？
EN: When you have done something wrong, why not admit it and apologize?

ZH: 何必为了一点小钱而伤害他人的感情呢？
EN: Why hurt someone's feelings for a small amount of money?

ZH: 何必纠结于过去的错误，积极面对未来才是明智之选。
EN: Why dwell on past mistakes when it's wiser to face the future positively?

ZH: 有些事情，何必太过计较，人生无法事事如意。
EN: For some things, why bother being too calculative? Life can't always go as planned.

ZH: 何必追求所有人的认可和赞赏，最重要的是自己的认同。
EN: Why pursue everyone's recognition and praise? The most important thing is self-approval.

ZH: 他已经不爱你了，何必继续为他付出呢？
EN: He doesn't love you anymore. Why continue to invest in him?

ZH: 何必为了别人的意见而改变自己的想法？
EN: Why change your own thoughts based on other people's opinions?

ZH: 何必为了虚荣心而不断攀比，那样永无止境。
EN: Why constantly compare yourself with others for the sake of vanity? It's endless.

ZH: 他明明对你不好，何必再次给他机会伤害你呢？
EN: He treated you badly, so why give him another chance to hurt you?

ZH: 何必一直扮演着别人期待的角色，活成自己真实的样子才是最好的。
EN: Why keep playing the role others expect of you? Being true to yourself is the best.

ZH: 何必每天追逐名利，有时候安静地享受生活才是真正的幸福。
EN: Why chase fame and fortune every day? Sometimes, quietly enjoying life is true happiness.

ZH: 他们决定放弃了，何必再抱着一丝幻想呢？
EN: They have decided to give up, so why still hold onto a glimmer of hope?
